<div id="Idea_4345"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaTitle">
<a href="/akira/dtd/4345-4049"><span id="IdeaTitle_4345">Department of Waste&nbsp;</span></a>
</div>
<table width=@%">  <tr>    <td valign="top"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaSubTitle"><b><a href="http://opengov.ideascale.com/akira/pmd/9481-4049">stevensje</a></b> <span class="IdeaScale_SecondaryText">3 hours ago</span></div></td>    <td align="right" valign="top"></td>  </tr></table>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaContent">Since waste has become such a problem to our society we We need to have a agency who can address the ever increasing problems. <br/><br/>They could be under the EPA or working together, etc. <br/><br/>They should also have law powers against pollutors, dumpers, etc. <br/><br/>We should not allow our country business, etc. to dump off waste foreign countries in the ocean, etc. Nor they us. <br/><br/>We could demand products such as plastic toys be recycleable and of a similar type. Same with hospital waste plastics, etc. <br/><br/>We have so much waste they should also monitor and be given funds to do research, recycle here making new produts, or sell our garage to other countries. There is profit in those dump yards and land sites. </div>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaFooter"><span style="border-right: 1px solid silver; margin:0 10px 0 0; padding: 0 5px 0 0; color: #666;"><a id="DiscussionTopic_4345" href="javascript:ajaxLink('DiscussionTopicComment_4345', '/akira/discussion.do?mode=comment&dbid=2248&topicID=4345')">Comments (1)</a></span><span id="DiscussionTopicTag_4345"><a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?discussionID=2248">Public-Private Partnerships</a></span></div><div style="margin-top:3px;" id="DiscussionTopicComment_4345"></div>
