<div id="Idea_4075"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaTitle">
<a href="/akira/dtd/4075-4049"><span id="IdeaTitle_4075">Community Audits to Identify At-Risk Populations and Pro-Active Intervention While Eliminating Duplication of Effort&nbsp;</span></a>
</div>
<table width=@%">  <tr>    <td valign="top"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaSubTitle"><b><a href="http://opengov.ideascale.com/akira/pmd/9451-4049">kkelly</a></b> <span class="IdeaScale_SecondaryText">1 day ago</span></div></td>    <td align="right" valign="top"></td>  </tr></table>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaContent">Create regional community audits, by identifying key demographics, community services, existing outreach networks, faith-based facilities, educational programs and research initiatives, population breakdowns, local industry and commerce, tourist and area attractions, public lands and transit, existing needs audit, and Continuum of Care services in areas of primary areas of concern such as mental health services, health care, senior services, disability resources, criminal justice, for these are areas where social services often overlap and interconnect.</div>
